, CT, where he assumed the name of James Davids."],"variants":[]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Dixwell was born about 1425, in Bedfordshire, England. He had at least 1 son with Margaret Sampson , Heiress. He died after 1449."},"et":{"about 1425–after 1449":"umbes 1425–pärast 1449","1427–1449":"1427–1449","1450–1472":"1450–1472","1425–1449":"1425–1449","1425":"1425","after 1449":"pärast 1449","about 1425":"umbes 1425","1472":"1472","1450":"1450","about 1450":"umbes 1450","1449":"1449","1427":"1427","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, England","Cotton, Staffordshire, England":"Cotton, Staffordshire, England"},"fi":{"about 1425–after 1449":"noin 1425–1449 jälkeen","1427–1449":"1427–1449","1450–1472":"1450–1472","1425–1449":"1425–1449","1425":"1425","after 1449":"1449 jälkeen","about 1425":"noin 1425","1472":"1472","1450":"1450","about 1450":"noin 1450","1449":"1449","1427":"1427","Bedfordshire, England":"Bedfordshire, England","Cotton, Staffordshire, England":"Cotton, Staffordshire, England"},"fr":{"about 1425–after 1449":"environ 1425–après 1449","1427–1449":"1427–1449","1450–1472":"1450–1472","1425–1449":"1425–1449","1425":"1425","after 1449":"après 1449","about 1425":"environ 1425","1472":"1472","1450":"1450","a